description.text:
You may want to adjust box and bolt to account for your printer's ability to make accurate holes.  
While you are testing, go to the very bottom and take the comments (//) off of these lines:  
//difference() {<br />
main();<br />
// translate([-1,-1,.6]) cube([100,100,100]);<br />
//}  
This will let you print just a thin test sheet. Or if you take the comment off the projection line, you can export to DXF and print to see if everything lines up well.
